update Landscape to calix.local dns domain



Gathering info needed to udpate landscape FQDN and FQDN  DNS update.
 A)   Change hostname from pln-landscape01.caal.dev to
pln-landscape01.calix.local hostnamectl set-hostname pln-landscape01.calix.local
B)  Edit Mail configuration and update all entries with new hostname
/etc/postfix/main.cf and run below commands.
sudo postmap main.cf
sudo systemctl reload postfix
C)  Web server configuration, disable site on old hostname and enable enable it on new hostname
Disable site


sudo a2dissite pln-landscape01.caal.dev
 
cd /etc/apache2/sites-available
mv pln-landscape01.caal.dev.conf pln-landscape01.calix.local.conf
edit /etc/apache2/sites-available/pln-landscape01.calix.local.conf
   ServerName pln-landscape01.calix.local
   ServerAdmin webmaster@pln-landscape01.calix.local
   ServerName pln-landscape01.calix.local
   ServerAdmin webmaster@pln-landscape01.calix.local
   ServerName pln-landscape01.calix.local
   ServerAdmin webmaster@pln-landscape01.calix.local
  Enable site
Sudo a2dissite pln-landscape01.calix.local
Reload new configuration
Sudo systemctl reload apache2
D)  Update and install TLS Certificate of the new FQDN
Setting up  ssl certificate.
Create .conf file
vi landscape_server.conf
[ req ]
default_md = sha256
prompt = no
req_extensions = req_ext
distinguished_name = req_distinguished_name
[ req_distinguished_name ]
commonName = vault.calix.local
countryName = US
stateOrProvinceName = California
localityName = San Jose
organizationName = Calix
organizationalUnitName = Engineering Operations
[ req_ext ]
subjectAltName = @alt_names
[ alt_names ]
DNS.0 = pln-landscape.calix.local
DNS.1 = pln-landscape
Run openssl
openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes -keyout landscape_server.key -out landscape_server.csr -config landscape_server.conf
Verify csr file
openssl req -text -noout -verify -in landscape_server.csr
 
Copy output of landscape_server.crs and request 2 years certificate from certificate request center; https://corp_pki.calix.local/certsrv/certrqxt.asp
Download certificates, convert .p7b to .pem and move to appropriate location.
Openssl pkcs7 -print_certs -in certnew.p7b -out landscape_server.pem
/etc/ssl/private/landscape_server.key
/etc/ssl/certs/landscape_server.pem
/etc/ssl/certs/landscape_server_ca.crt




